    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#boardman-hayes1966"/>, p. 169 n. <citedRange>998</citedRange> (ph., dr.)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/>, pp. 253-255, <citedRange>m</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#mei2013"/>, p. <citedRange>21</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>63.1730</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>001925</citedRange></bibl>.
                Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2015a"/>, p. <citedRange>66</citedRange></bibl>.</p>             
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Κώκιος">Ϙōκίο̄</name></persName> <g type="punct">|</g>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem resp="#cdl1970">Ϙο̄κίο̄</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#boardman-hayes1966">φōκιο</rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#boardman-hayes1966">ϙōκιο</rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#boardman-hayes1966">Ῥōκιο</rdg>
                </app>
                    <app loc="1"><lem><g type="punct">|</g></lem>
                    <rdg resp="#bordman-hayes1966"> <note>Boardman did not mention this sign</note></rdg>
                </app>
                </p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">J'appartiens à</supplied> Kôkios.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">I belong to</supplied> Kokios.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Proprietà di</supplied> Kokios.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/></bibl> did non include it into the Cyrenaean items. However, as <foreign xml:lang="grc">ϙ</foreign> is now better attested,
                    this might be after all have been inscribed in Cyrenaica.</p>
                <p>At right end of the graffito, a vertical stroke extending to the left at top resembles no Greek letter and might be a sort of final punct. This sign
                is not commented upon by ed. princ.</p>
                <p>The new personal name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Κώκιος</foreign> was discussed by <bibl><ptr target="#cdl1970"/></bibl>  with reference to <bibl><ptr target="#robert1963"/>, p. <citedRange>312-320</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
